I) a Roman Catholic priest who acts for another higher-ranking clergyman
II) (Episcopal Church) a clergyman in charge of a chapel
III) (Church of England) a clergyman appointed to act as priest of a parish

The answer is: III

 Decades of educational research tell us unequivocally that even smaller classes have zero effect on the academic performance of the pupils -- though they may sometimes be desirable for other reasons .

I) not the same one or ones already mentioned or implied; - the White Queen
II) recently past
III) belonging to the distant past
IV) very unusual; different in character or quality from the normal or expected; - Lance Morrow

Do not provide explanations. Just output the choice.
RESULT:  IV) very unusual; different in character or quality from the normal or expected; - Lance Morrow
The answer is: IV
Gold answer is: 1
Attempted: 1962, Correct: 1199, Accuracy: 0.6111111111111112
